devdoc.author: Noah Zinsmeister
devdoc.details: O(1) insertion, removal, contains, and length functions.

params.other: The element to check membership of.
params.self: The set to check membership in.

contains(AddressSet.Set storage,address).return: true if the element is in the set, false otherwise.

insert(AddressSet.Set storage,address).details: Inserts an element into a set. If the element already exists in the set, the function is a no-op.

length(AddressSet.Set storage).details: Returns the number of elements in a set.

params.self: The set to check the length of.

length(AddressSet.Set storage).return: The number of elements in the set.

remove(AddressSet.Set storage,address).details: Removes an element from a set. If the element does not exist in the set, the function is a no-op.

devdoc.title: An implementation of the set data structure for addresses.
